    "text": "[IES·bPrP] and [lES·2bPrP] complexes are still present, albeit in a much lower quantity. In the reference experiment (Fig. 4A), if one assumes that the peaks from the two complexes represent 100% of the intensity of the signal, the two peaks corresponding to the complexes with bPrP in only 36 and 42%, respectively, of the total intensity of all three peaks. This suggests that these peptides effectively compete with bPrP for binding with the antibody.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
